{
  "texts": [
    "2 Supplemental Section A provides a full nomenclature reference; see Tables 2, 3, and 4.",
    "Let [r] denote the set of integers {1, …, r}.",
    "A m ∼B denotes that the cardinality of set A is m and that A is drawn uniformly at random (u.a.r.) from set B.",
    "For singleton set A (i.e., |A| = 1), the sampling notation is simplified to A ∼ B.",
    "Let 2 A denote the power set of any set A."
  ]
}